[[File:2018-04-23 ZDF Bela Rethy-6968.jpg|thumb|Béla Réthy (2018)]] '''Béla Andreas Réthy''' (born 14 December 1956 in [[Vienna]]) is a [[Germany|German]] sports reporter of [[Hungary|Hungarian]] ancestry.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.discogs.com/artist/Bela+Reti|title=''Bela Reti''|work=www.discogs.com|accessdate=13 February 2010}}</ref>
When Réthy was born, his parents had to leave their home country because of the [[Hungarian Revolution of 1956|1956 Hungarian Revolution]]. They emigrated to [[Brazil]] where they stayed until they went to [[Germany]] in 1968.<ref name="berner">{{cite web |url=http://www.berner-block.de/Bela-Rethy.80.0.html |title=''Bela Rethy'' |work=www.berner-block.de |language=German |accessdate=13 February 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100618030714/http://www.berner-block.de/Bela-Rethy.80.0.html |archivedate=18 June 2010 |df= }}</ref> Réthy obtained his ''[[Abitur]]'' certificate so he was able to attend [[Johannes Gutenberg University of Mainz]] where he studied [[literature]] and [[journalism]]. In the meantime he worked in the sports archive of the [[ZDF]] and became a [[freelancer]] later. Since 1987, he has been salaried.
His first live broadcast was during an international football match between the under-16 teams of [[Germany]] and [[Ireland]] in 1991. He has commentated the finals of:<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.pressetreff.zdf.de/download.asp?attid=57400&.doc |title=''Béla Réthy - Biographie'' |publisher=pressetreff.zdf.de |work=[[ZDF]] |language=German |accessdate=13 February 2010 }}{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>
* the [[UEFA Euro 1996|Euro 1996]] ([[Germany]] vs. [[Czech Republic]]) in [[England]] * the [[2002 FIFA World Cup]] (Germany vs. [[Brazil]]) in [[Japan]] and [[South Korea]] * the [[UEFA Euro 2004|Euro 2004]] ([[Portugal]] vs. [[Greece]]) in Portugal
Réthy speaks German, Hungarian, Portuguese and English fluently, as well as French and Spanish.<ref name="berner"/>
