{{Unreferenced|date=January 2014}}

The '''Chilean national inline hockey team''' represents [[Roller in-line hockey|inline hockey]] in [[Chile]] at international competitions. The team have not played in any world championships until the [[Chilean Ice and Inline Hockey Federation]] was founded and it joined the [[International Ice Hockey Federation|IIHF]] in 2000. The team does however participate in the [[IIHF Inline Hockey World Championship]] and the [[FIRS Inline Hockey World Championships|FIRS Inline Hockey World Championship]] tournaments (organised by [[Fédération Internationale de Roller Sports|International Roller Sports Federation]]). Chile has rinks in [[Santiago]], [[Puerto Montt]], and [[Punta Arenas]], where [[ice hockey]] is being developed.

