'''Club Deportivo Maldonado''' is a [[football (soccer)|football]] club from [[Maldonado, Uruguay]]. They currently play in the [[Uruguayan Segunda División]].

==History==
[[Image:Cd maldonado.png|thumb|logo of the parent sports club]]
Club Deportivo Maldonado, SAD have a history of being a ''Middle Men'' club used by  [[Third-party ownership in association football|third-party owners]], where top flight South American clubs will sell players to the team before they are immediately sold or loaned to another club, with the player never appearing for Deportivo Maldonado. Notable players who've made this type of transfer include [[Jonathan Calleri]], [[Gerónimo Rulli]], [[Hernán Toledo]], [[Alex Sandro]], [[Marcelo Estigarribia]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Welcome to Deportivo Maldonado, where the big names never actually play|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2016/oct/10/deportivo-maldonado-stars-never-play-calleri-riulli-agents|work=The Guardian|accessdate=11 December 2016|date=10 October 2016}}</ref> [[Willian José]]<ref>{{cite news|title=Tiny Uruguayan soccer club makes millions as undercover transfer market middle-man|url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2014/03/deportivo-maldonado-uruguay-soccer-club-middle-man-transfers|website=usatoday.com|publisher=USA Today|accessdate=11 December 2016|date=19 March 2014|others=Bloomberg and transfermarkt contributed the content}}</ref> and [[Iván Piris]].<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.asroma.it/pdf/corporate/operazioni_di_mercato/2012_-_08_-1_Piris.pdf|title=IVAN RODRIGO PIRIS Operazioni di mercato|date=1 August 2012|accessdate=3 August 2012|publisher=A.S. Roma|language=Italian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130214142443/http://www.asroma.it/pdf/corporate/operazioni_di_mercato/2012_-_08_-1_Piris.pdf|archivedate=14 February 2013}}</ref>

