eonato Carioca|Rio de Janeiro]] state leagues. |- |Netherlands||1954<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/region-netherlands.html |title=Netherlands – Regional Analysis |last=Stokkermans |first=Karel |year=2015 |publisher=Rec.Sport.Soccer Statistics Foundation}}</ref>|| |- |West Germany||1963<ref>[http://footballrepublik.com/bundesliga-50-the-birth-of-the-professional-game/ BUNDESLIGA 50 – The birth of Germany's Professional Game.] Christoph Wagner | FootballRepublik.com .</ref>||{{main|Introduction of the Bundesliga}} |- |Sweden||1967<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gih.se/documents/cif/tidningen/2005/4_2005/svif054%20s38-43%20wickberg.pdf|title=Amatör eller professionist?|publisher=GIH|language=Swedish|year=2005|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006071424/http://www.gih.se/documents/cif/tidningen/2005/4_2005/svif054%20s38-43%20wickberg.pdf|archivedate=2014-10-06|df=}}</ref>|| |- |Denmark||1978<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dbu.dk/oevrigt_indhold/Om%20DBU/DBUs%20historie/dbus_historie_1961-1980.aspx|title=DBU's historie 1961-1980 |publisher=[[Dansk Boldspil-Union]]|language=Danish |year=2002}}</ref>|| |- |Norway||1992<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dagbladet.no/2009/08/07/sport/fotball/tippeligaen/europacup/7548836/|title=Alle heiet underveis|last=Sæther|first=Esten O.|date=7 August 2009|work=Dagbladet|language=Norwegian|accessdate=8 August 2009}}</ref>|| |- |}
