{{Infobox venue | name = Vångavallen | nickname = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | fullname = | former names = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = Vångavallen 20120806 00390.jpg | image_size = 200px | image_alt = | caption = Vångavallen under floodlights | pushpin_map = | pushpin_mapsize = | pushpin_map_caption = | pushpin_label_position = | address = | location = [[Trelleborg]], [[Sweden]] | coordinates = | type = [[sports ground]] | genre = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = {{Start date|df=y|1933|6|5}} | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | seating_type = | capacity = 7,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | field_shape = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = [[Trelleborgs FF]] | embedded = | website = | publictransit = }} '''Vångavallen''' is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] in [[Trelleborg]], [[Sweden]]. It is currently used mostly for [[Association football|football]] matches and is the home stadium of [[Trelleborgs FF]]. The stadium was opened on 5 June 1933.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.trelleborg.se/sv/kommun-politik/kommunfakta/trelleborgs-historia/trelleborg-i-artal1/1933-75-arsjubilarer-lika-aktuella-idag/|title=1933 - 75-årsjubilarer lika aktuella idag|publisher=Trelleborg Municipality|language=Swedish|date=January 2013|accessdate=10 October 2016}}</ref> It has a capacity of 7,000 spectators, 3,000 of which is seated.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.trelleborgsff.se/foreningen/vangavallen|publisher=Trelleborgs FF |language=Swedish |accessdate=2018-02-27|title=Vångavallen}}</ref>
